title: First presidency of Donald Trump
added: By November 6, a growing number of Trump officials had admitted that the incumbent's loss was probable.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Orr|first=Gabby|last2=McGraw|first2=Meridith|date=2020-11-06|title='My sense is that we lost': Trump campaign aides grapple with dwindling odds|url=https://www.politico.com/news/2020/11/06/trump-campaign-aides-reality-434785|url-status=live|access-date=2020-11-07|website=Politico|language=en}}</ref> On that day, election-calling organization [[Decision Desk HQ]] forecast that Trump had lost the election to Biden.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Prokop |first1=Andrew |title=Why Decision Desk called Pennsylvania, and the presidential race, for Joe Biden |url=https://www.vox.com/21552641/joe-biden-wins-pennsylvania-decision-desk |accessdate=November 7, 2020 |work=[[Vox (website)|Vox]] |date=November 6, 2020}}</ref>
